Macron Causes Stir as He Vows to ‚ÄúPiss Off‚Äù France‚Äôs Unvaccinated ‚Äúto the Bitter End‚Äù

üá´üá∑@COVID19Up: French President Emmanuel Macron raised eyebrows and provoked shock on Tuesday (Jan. 4) when he warned unvaccinated people in France that he would purposely get on their nerves by limiting access to key aspects of life.

‚ÄúI don‚Äôt want to piss the French people off‚Ä¶ But as for the non-vaccinated, I really want to piss them off. And we will continue to do this, to the end. This is the strategy,‚Äù he told the Le Parisien newspaper. The president added that this would mean ‚Äúlimiting as much as possible their access to activities in social life."

"You have to say to them: from January 15 you can no longer go to a restaurant, you can no longer go for a drink, you can no longer go for a coffee, you can no longer go to the theatre, you can no longer go to the cinema," he went on.

Macron's remarks brought immediate condemnation from political rivals, including likely opponents in the upcoming election. Eric Zemmour and Marine Le Pen both criticized the president, Le Pen accusing him of "persisting in division" and of seeking to "make the non-vaccinated second-class citizens."

The French parliament is currently debating turning the "health pass" into a "vaccine pass" which would prevent unvaccinated people from accessing most public indoor spaces, even with a negative SARS-CoV-2 test.
